22
00:04:29.853 --> 00:04:30.649
Hey there.

23
00:04:31.053 --> 00:04:32.008
Drop dead.

24
00:04:34.973 --> 00:04:37.407
- What a beauty!
- A real peach.


25
00:04:39.453 --> 00:04:40.772
Such beautiful eyes.

26
00:04:41.573 --> 00:04:42.847
The veil suits you.

27
00:04:43.093 --> 00:04:44.367
Don't be shy.

28
00:04:44.733 --> 00:04:45.722
You don't like us?

29
00:04:45.973 --> 00:04:47.645
Mr Bechir, come here.

30
00:04:47.893 --> 00:04:49.531
But it's only you we want.

31
00:04:51.013 --> 00:04:52.765
Need some help, boys?

32
00:04:53.013 --> 00:04:56.050
Beat it, Noura.
This isn't kids stuff.


33
00:04:57.133 --> 00:04:59.249
It's no use, forget it.

34
00:04:59.493 --> 00:05:00.642
Already?

35
00:05:01.213 --> 00:05:02.612
She's looking at us.

36
00:05:02.933 --> 00:05:05.891
- Shall we go to the beach?
- Get lost.


37
00:05:06.573 --> 00:05:08.165
The holidays are almost over.

38
00:05:08.413 --> 00:05:10.449
Go and dig yourself a grave then.

39
00:05:12.173 --> 00:05:14.403
- Plenty more fish in the sea.
- Hopefully.


40
00:05:17.373 --> 00:05:18.692
Buzz off!

41
00:05:20.013 --> 00:05:21.731
You're delicious.

42
00:05:21.973 --> 00:05:23.884
Go and find something to do.

43
00:05:24.333 --> 00:05:26.801
- God, you're gorgeous.
- Incredible!


44
00:05:27.133 --> 00:05:28.168
Drop dead.

45
00:05:29.413 --> 00:05:33.042
- Are you in a hurry?
- I'm free right now.


46
00:05:37.773 --> 00:05:39.491
Give us some more, gorgeous.

47
00:05:39.733 --> 00:05:41.246
More what?

48
00:05:41.493 --> 00:05:43.882
The veil looks great on you.

49
00:05:44.573 --> 00:05:46.291
And you'd look great dead.

50
00:05:46.533 --> 00:05:49.889
- When can we become engaged?
- You? With your face?


51
00:05:51.613 --> 00:05:55.242
- My brother would sort you out.
- How?


52
00:05:55.493 --> 00:05:56.926
Watch out!

53
00:05:57.453 --> 00:05:59.171
Noura! Come here.

54
00:06:14.573 --> 00:06:17.371
You're nothing but hooligans!

55
00:06:39.453 --> 00:06:42.013
Get a move on.

56
00:06:43.253 --> 00:06:44.891
Noura, look over there.

57
00:07:03.693 --> 00:07:06.651
<i>This cup of love</i>

58
00:07:06.893 --> 00:07:10.249
<i>We share you and me</i>

59
00:07:10.733 --> 00:07:13.964
<i>Will make us both merry</i>

60
00:07:14.213 --> 00:07:18.491
Where did Lilia hide her boy-friend
this time?


61
00:07:19.453 --> 00:07:22.286
- Can't you forget that affair?
- What happened?


62
00:07:22.533 --> 00:07:27.448
She pulled the wool over her father's
eyes. She hid him in the attic.


63
00:07:29.533 --> 00:07:31.808
She told her father his shoes
were her brother's.


64
00:07:32.053 --> 00:07:36.012
- Isn't her brother abroad?
- Well, her father's an old man.


65
00:07:36.253 --> 00:07:40.371
- The poor old fellow.
- Whatever will she think up next?


66
00:07:40.973 --> 00:07:44.682
- Somebody's coming.
- Who? Aunt Zuleika?


67
00:07:46.093 --> 00:07:48.687
She looks so innocent

68
00:07:49.293 --> 00:07:51.966
but she did worse when she was young!

69
00:07:53.453 --> 00:07:56.889
- Come and help us.
- Pick up the bottles.


70
00:08:11.333 --> 00:08:12.288
Hands off!

71
00:08:14.333 --> 00:08:15.971
There's still wine in it.

72
00:08:37.173 --> 00:08:38.447
Six bottles.

73
00:08:42.813 --> 00:08:43.882
All perfect.

74
00:08:47.933 --> 00:08:49.571
What about this one?

75
00:08:55.093 --> 00:08:58.802
The police raided Ali's place
last night.


76
00:08:59.053 --> 00:09:01.613
Took his radio and ate his food.

77
00:09:01.853 --> 00:09:04.242
Wasn't he supposed
to come here today?


78
00:09:04.493 --> 00:09:07.166
Must have gone somewhere else
for a drink.


79
00:09:09.893 --> 00:09:12.327
One, two, three.

80
00:09:13.213 --> 00:09:16.410
- One more!
- You're never satisfied.


81
00:09:17.213 --> 00:09:18.441
Thanks.

82
00:09:24.173 --> 00:09:25.447
Next time, watch out.

83
00:09:32.893 --> 00:09:34.804
These pens never leave me.

84
00:09:35.053 --> 00:09:38.887
You need to look educated
if you want a girl.


85
00:09:55.053 --> 00:10:00.047
Take this to Salih
before he drops off to sleep.


86
00:10:06.493 --> 00:10:07.448
Is that all?

87
00:10:11.693 --> 00:10:12.887
What about me?

88
00:10:13.293 --> 00:10:16.649
Ill-gotten gains aren't for kids.

89
00:10:16.893 --> 00:10:18.690
I'll tell Salih of you.

90
00:10:24.013 --> 00:10:26.846
Noura, buy me some cigarettes.

91
00:10:27.093 --> 00:10:29.243
Sorry, Mr Sadok, 
I'm doing a job.

92
00:10:30.093 --> 00:10:32.687
A kilo of potatoes, love?

93
00:10:42.373 --> 00:10:45.251
Want a dip, Noura?

94
00:10:45.533 --> 00:10:47.967
I'm not a kid any more.

95
00:10:51.733 --> 00:10:57.091
Doins errands for Salih again?
What's he got that we haven't?


96
00:10:57.333 --> 00:10:58.607
Ahmed, I'm in a hurry.

97
00:10:58.853 --> 00:11:02.129
Let's see, is it perfume?

98
00:11:02.373 --> 00:11:04.728
Can't I have some?

99
00:11:05.413 --> 00:11:09.122
There you go, hopping off again!

100
00:11:10.413 --> 00:11:14.531
SALIH'S FOR SHOES,
THEATRE AND SONGS


101
00:11:34.253 --> 00:11:38.212
If it isn't Noura.
There's no one to touch you.


102
00:11:38.453 --> 00:11:41.126
Goods delivered on time.

103
00:11:41.373 --> 00:11:46.891
I'm writing a play about some Europeans
who never sober up.


104
00:11:47.133 --> 00:11:48.691
I'm not joking.

105
00:11:50.173 --> 00:11:52.243
- It's written?
- Yes.


106
00:11:52.933 --> 00:11:57.768
Except for the title.
I may call it "Laughter in the Dark".


107
00:11:59.493 --> 00:12:01.245
Put that inside.

108
00:12:33.573 --> 00:12:36.326
I brought that from Singapore.

109
00:12:36.573 --> 00:12:40.885
I used it in my famous play,
"Picnic in Istanbul".


110
00:12:41.973 --> 00:12:45.852
Nowadays it seems you young people
can't settle to anything.


111
00:12:46.573 --> 00:12:49.531
It's all Moncef's and Mounir's fault.

112
00:12:50.053 --> 00:12:52.169
They treat me like a baby.

113
00:12:52.413 --> 00:12:54.244
Listen to me.

114
00:12:54.493 --> 00:12:59.328
A man proposes
but it's the woman who disposes.


115
00:12:59.773 --> 00:13:01.604
But how will I know?

116
00:13:01.853 --> 00:13:04.162
She'll soon show you.

117
00:13:08.453 --> 00:13:10.762
Run along.
Here comes my actress.


118
00:13:17.893 --> 00:13:20.088
Welcome, my dear customer.

119
00:13:29.533 --> 00:13:31.842
Today, I've just what you want.

120
00:13:32.093 --> 00:13:33.446
I wonder.

121
00:13:35.733 --> 00:13:38.930
I know your fitting. Come inside.

122
00:13:41.373 --> 00:13:43.091
Take all the time you want.

123
00:13:44.173 --> 00:13:49.611
I'm hard to please. What makes you
so sure your goods will please me?


124
00:13:49.853 --> 00:13:51.844
Not everything is on display.

125
00:13:52.493 --> 00:13:53.721
Suppose I'm disappointed?

126
00:13:54.213 --> 00:13:57.603
Everything I have is made to measure.

127
00:14:29.933 --> 00:14:31.844
I was looking for you.

128
00:14:40.453 --> 00:14:45.322
I've brought you a fantastic
fountain pen. It still works.


129
00:14:45.573 --> 00:14:48.645
You're old enough
to find the ink yourself.


130
00:14:53.173 --> 00:14:55.482
What's his new play called?

131
00:14:55.733 --> 00:14:59.646
Can't you hear?
"Laughter in the Dark".


132
00:15:00.573 --> 00:15:05.124
In the dark? Really?
You're not pulling my leg?


133
00:15:11.773 --> 00:15:16.563
How dare you pester girls.
Mixing with those hooligans!


134
00:15:17.293 --> 00:15:18.726
Dad, don't hurt me.

135
00:15:22.253 --> 00:15:25.609
I've got diabetes.
And you're out to kill me.


136
00:15:28.293 --> 00:15:30.807
I don't see a single tear.

137
00:15:31.053 --> 00:15:33.089
Cry before I kill you.

138
00:15:34.813 --> 00:15:37.407
Please, Azzouz, forgive him.

139
00:15:38.533 --> 00:15:41.684
For my sake, let him off.

140
00:15:41.933 --> 00:15:43.605
I'm leaving then.

141
00:15:46.653 --> 00:15:48.644
Tomorrow he starts at the barber's.

142
00:16:01.653 --> 00:16:03.848
Won't you try some of my sweets?

143
00:16:04.653 --> 00:16:05.722
Right now?

144
00:16:06.493 --> 00:16:08.211
You'll be the first.

145
00:16:08.933 --> 00:16:10.161
Are you sure?

146
00:16:14.533 --> 00:16:15.761
I'll try just one.

147
00:16:24.253 --> 00:16:28.246
The last thing you gave me
didn't work, sheikh.


148
00:16:28.493 --> 00:16:30.688
I still have nightmares.

149
00:16:30.933 --> 00:16:34.767
I have just what you need.

150
00:16:35.053 --> 00:16:39.251
Every night I have this terrible
powerless feeling.


151
00:16:45.373 --> 00:16:47.125
Put this against your breast.

152
00:16:47.453 --> 00:16:51.810
You will be very calm
and you'll sleep soundly.


153
00:16:52.293 --> 00:16:54.409
What would I do without you?

154
00:16:59.333 --> 00:17:02.405
Rest assured, I'll keep it close.

155
00:17:03.813 --> 00:17:05.849
What's the ogre doing with the blood?

156
00:17:06.093 --> 00:17:10.928
He's tracking the blood, drop by drop,
to Aisha's house.


157
00:17:11.173 --> 00:17:15.166
Then he takes hold of her little brother

158
00:17:15.413 --> 00:17:18.291
and scrunches him all up.

159
00:17:18.533 --> 00:17:23.288
- Why does he need a golden needle?
- Because Aisha's a virgin.


160
00:17:23.533 --> 00:17:26.570
The ogre knows it's forbidden.

161
00:17:27.053 --> 00:17:30.284
If he touches a virgin,
his hands will burn.


162
00:17:30.533 --> 00:17:33.923
If he lifts her dress, he'll go blind.

163
00:17:34.173 --> 00:17:37.802
The ogre is only interested
in children of your age.


164
00:17:38.293 --> 00:17:43.162
Little boys like you
he scrunches down to the last bone.


165
00:18:42.133 --> 00:18:44.442
You're the ones talking rubbish.

166
00:18:44.693 --> 00:18:50.484
Take good citizen Hamadi Samema
who's sitting right here.


167
00:18:50.733 --> 00:18:53.327
Hamadi Carama, please.

168
00:18:54.253 --> 00:18:57.802
Allah planned to make him a rat

169
00:18:58.973 --> 00:19:02.363
but the angels intervened
and here's the result.


170
00:19:02.693 --> 00:19:05.844
Do you mind,
show some respect for my uniform!


171
00:19:06.093 --> 00:19:07.412
A rat, a rat.

172
00:19:09.453 --> 00:19:11.728
- Carama, if you please!
- Rat.


173
00:19:18.653 --> 00:19:21.804
Release our comrades!

174
00:19:39.653 --> 00:19:42.372
Get on with your work.

175
00:19:45.653 --> 00:19:50.773
More trouble again. Soon they'll be
whining again for forgiveness.


176
00:19:51.013 --> 00:19:55.291
Come on, Abdelwahab,
they say some people were killed.


177
00:19:57.133 --> 00:19:58.248
It's a fact.

178
00:19:58.493 --> 00:19:59.642
As for me,

179
00:20:01.013 --> 00:20:05.291
I only believe what I read
in the paper.


180
00:20:05.813 --> 00:20:10.364
People killed!
People die of diabetes too.


181
00:20:10.773 --> 00:20:13.333
You can die in lots of ways.

182
00:20:13.973 --> 00:20:16.692
Shut up, here comes Colombo.

183
00:20:23.213 --> 00:20:26.444
Look what the wind's blown in.

184
00:20:26.693 --> 00:20:29.048
Do you want a free shave?

185
00:20:29.653 --> 00:20:31.371
What's all this?

186
00:20:31.693 --> 00:20:33.604
It's hardly the moment.

187
00:20:33.933 --> 00:20:36.766
I'm looking for Youssef Soltane.

188
00:20:37.733 --> 00:20:39.325
Was he here this morning?

189
00:20:39.853 --> 00:20:41.332
What's he done to you?

190
00:20:42.013 --> 00:20:45.642
Did he try to overthrow your regime?

191
00:20:46.093 --> 00:20:47.606
Stop fooling around.

192
00:20:47.853 --> 00:20:51.641
My boss is so exacting,
I need the man dead or alive.


193
00:20:52.173 --> 00:20:55.609
He's causing us a lot of trouble.

194
00:20:56.133 --> 00:21:00.012
To think we ever considered him
one of us.


195
00:21:00.773 --> 00:21:06.643
Tell your boss we're all on his side.

196
00:21:06.893 --> 00:21:09.805
If anyone sticks their neck out,

197
00:21:10.053 --> 00:21:13.170
we'll be pleased to give them a chop.

198
00:21:14.533 --> 00:21:15.761
Believe me.

199
00:21:18.533 --> 00:21:21.809
- Shut up the shop, there's trouble.
- Dad won't like it.


200
00:21:22.053 --> 00:21:24.408
Shut up as quick as you can.

201
00:21:24.653 --> 00:21:25.847
Get a move on!

202
00:21:45.133 --> 00:21:46.407
That hurts.

203
00:21:48.453 --> 00:21:52.731
That's nothing compared
with this morning. All hell was loose.


204
00:21:52.973 --> 00:21:56.249
The police came.
They nearly broke the shop window.


205
00:21:56.493 --> 00:21:57.687
It's begun again?

206
00:21:57.933 --> 00:22:01.562
I don't like this summerjob.
There's no need for you to go.


207
00:22:01.813 --> 00:22:05.089
You can help with your brother's
circumcision.


208
00:22:43.533 --> 00:22:45.603
Noura, what are you doing here?

209
00:22:45.853 --> 00:22:47.571
I came to see Salih.

210
00:22:49.493 --> 00:22:51.529
Hello, sheikh, what's this?

211
00:22:51.773 --> 00:22:56.483
Out shopping like one of us?
Is there a bottle in that basket?


212
00:22:56.733 --> 00:23:01.284
Drunkard! Your should repent
of your evil habit.


213
00:23:01.533 --> 00:23:04.889
May you never know its pleasures.

214
00:23:16.413 --> 00:23:18.085
Don't you dare!

215
00:23:18.853 --> 00:23:22.687
It's bad for you.
Don't let me ever catch you again.


216
00:23:31.693 --> 00:23:35.572
This boy was pestering the girls
in our street.


217
00:23:35.813 --> 00:23:38.373
Our girls don't need any pens.

218
00:23:39.293 --> 00:23:43.286
- How dare you hit him?
- Keep out of this.


219
00:23:44.173 --> 00:23:46.368
Take your hands off me.

220
00:23:46.613 --> 00:23:50.686
I don't believe it.
A big man like you attacking children!


221
00:23:50.933 --> 00:23:53.208
It'll be your turn soon.

222
00:23:53.453 --> 00:23:57.412
One day your impudent songs
will land you in jail.


223
00:23:57.653 --> 00:23:59.211
This is a new interest!

224
00:23:59.453 --> 00:24:03.207
You're starting to hit notes now
rather than people.


225
00:24:06.893 --> 00:24:10.886
I swear I'll clout him
unless he sings for me.


226
00:24:11.133 --> 00:24:13.328
I don't sing to animals.

227
00:24:14.053 --> 00:24:16.089
Tell him to sing.

228
00:24:16.333 --> 00:24:18.688
Sing, Salih, so we're rid of him.

229
00:24:18.933 --> 00:24:20.082
No way!

230
00:24:20.333 --> 00:24:21.891
I'll smash up your shop.

231
00:24:22.133 --> 00:24:24.328
Sing, he's getting angry.

232
00:24:24.813 --> 00:24:26.804
I'd rather die.

233
00:24:27.053 --> 00:24:29.283
We'll all sing for you.

234
00:24:29.533 --> 00:24:33.321
<i>I've picked you, my sweetest flower</i>

235
00:24:33.653 --> 00:24:37.282
<i>I've chosen you, my sweetest flower</i>

236
00:24:46.613 --> 00:24:47.648
What's going on?

237
00:24:50.813 --> 00:24:54.647
I was just having a joke with Salih.

238
00:24:55.373 --> 00:24:59.207
What, sweetie, don't you know
who the sweetest flower is?


239
00:24:59.453 --> 00:25:00.806
Or have you forgotten?

240
00:25:03.213 --> 00:25:06.444
When the cat's away,
the mice play, eh?


241
00:25:06.893 --> 00:25:08.485
Did you think I'd died?

242
00:25:08.733 --> 00:25:13.090
Why are you humiliating me?
I was only having a joke.


243
00:25:13.333 --> 00:25:14.971
I'm joking too.

244
00:25:15.573 --> 00:25:17.643
See how's he's grown up now.

245
00:25:19.413 --> 00:25:20.846
He's become a little man.

246
00:25:23.093 --> 00:25:27.166
He's even growing a beard.
Let me feel.


247
00:25:27.933 --> 00:25:30.242
Let's have a touch.

248
00:26:24.613 --> 00:26:26.604
Good grief, Salouha!

249
00:26:28.133 --> 00:26:30.283
Is all this your trousseau?

250
00:26:44.013 --> 00:26:46.402
Red really suits you.

251
00:27:26.453 --> 00:27:29.365
<i>Darling, be nice</i>

