I'll be in a trance soon.

504
01:04:12.893 --> 01:04:13.962
Come over here.

505
01:04:16.173 --> 01:04:19.563
- Have you seen Noura?
- We'll help you find him.


506
01:04:39.573 --> 01:04:42.770
Excuse me while I take
my cough syrup.


507
01:04:43.013 --> 01:04:45.004
Doctor's orders.

508
01:05:01.773 --> 01:05:07.325
<i>A woman loved me but I rejected her</i>

509
01:05:09.453 --> 01:05:12.650
<i>Now I'm in love
and the woman rejects me</i>


510
01:05:13.053 --> 01:05:16.841
<i>I was hard on
the woman who loved me</i>

511
01:05:17.093 --> 01:05:19.687
<i>Now my mistress is hard on me</i>

512
01:05:26.493 --> 01:05:30.532
<i>When I was loved I was unkind,
I showed no pity</i>


513
01:05:35.173 --> 01:05:38.848
<i>Today I'm paying for my wickedness</i>

514
01:05:46.213 --> 01:05:50.684
<i>I don't annoy her,
I don't pester her or beg</i>


515
01:05:50.933 --> 01:05:55.563
<i>But you reap what you sow</i>

516
01:05:55.813 --> 01:06:01.524
<i>Now, if anyone says they love me,
I say I love them too</i>


517
01:06:01.773 --> 01:06:04.526
<i>Where is love, where is love?</i>

518
01:06:14.613 --> 01:06:19.733
<i>No. I don't love you, I don't trust you,
you won't stay with me</i>


519
01:06:19.973 --> 01:06:22.533
<i>Even if I love you deep down</i>

520
01:06:25.573 --> 01:06:29.122
<i>I'll say the contrary</i>

521
01:06:45.413 --> 01:06:49.008
- Where's this talent been hiding?
- How very charming.


522
01:07:11.093 --> 01:07:12.765
This looks good.

523
01:07:13.453 --> 01:07:15.011
Very tasty.

524
01:07:15.453 --> 01:07:17.011
Stop being such pests.

525
01:07:17.253 --> 01:07:19.209
We're not doing anything.

526
01:07:33.294 --> 01:07:38.527
<i>All the friends and family
are gathered for the circumcision</i>


527
01:08:57.374 --> 01:08:59.251
I'm going for my injection.

528
01:08:59.774 --> 01:09:02.846
The man isn't their uncle,
he's a wizard.


529
01:09:03.094 --> 01:09:04.891
A robber of hearts.

530
01:09:05.574 --> 01:09:09.692
He goes out each night
looking for small children.


531
01:09:09.934 --> 01:09:14.086
When he finds one,
he puts him in his bag


532
01:09:14.414 --> 01:09:16.166
and takes him to a deserted place.

533
01:09:16.814 --> 01:09:19.851
There, he looks at the child's palm
for the mark.


534
01:09:20.094 --> 01:09:24.406
If he finds a ring there
or a white dot on his iris,


535
01:09:24.654 --> 01:09:29.125
he kills the child
and rips his heart out.


536
01:09:29.374 --> 01:09:34.812
Then he burns him to find the treasure
hidden in the earth.


537
01:09:51.934 --> 01:09:55.927
I wrote this play especially for you.

538
01:09:56.174 --> 01:09:59.405
Being an actress isn't just
a question of greasepaint.


539
01:09:59.654 --> 01:10:05.570
Whoever heard of a play written
for just two people?


540
01:10:05.814 --> 01:10:09.648
I'm not the kind of girl
you think I am.


541
01:10:11.614 --> 01:10:15.448
Why do you doubt my motives?
They're entirely honourable.


542
01:10:16.494 --> 01:10:21.773
I'm only thinking about art.
I've no evil intentions.


543
01:10:22.014 --> 01:10:27.042
I'm not that naive.
I may be divorced


544
01:10:27.294 --> 01:10:30.252
but I've a family and friends
to protect me.


545
01:10:30.894 --> 01:10:32.691
Is this gold?

546
01:10:33.214 --> 01:10:34.852
Stop that.

547
01:10:35.614 --> 01:10:37.013
Very well.

548
01:10:39.054 --> 01:10:43.445
God be my witness.
You made the first move.


549
01:12:52.814 --> 01:12:56.727
Hold your aunt's foot still
so we get the correct size.


550
01:12:58.654 --> 01:13:00.565
You need someone to help you.

551
01:13:02.094 --> 01:13:08.090
No, I manage very well alone.
It's much better that way.


552
01:13:08.734 --> 01:13:11.043
I'd like a pair of wedding shoes.

553
01:13:13.294 --> 01:13:17.003
Sorry, I don't stock
that type of footwear.


554
01:13:19.574 --> 01:13:21.292
What if a client

555
01:13:21.534 --> 01:13:24.332
is patient and willing to wait?

556
01:13:25.054 --> 01:13:26.726
The other foot, please.

557
01:13:59.934 --> 01:14:01.162
Leave them be.

558
01:14:02.974 --> 01:14:04.123
What are you doing?

559
01:14:27.694 --> 01:14:30.128
Seal it up properly.

560
01:14:31.614 --> 01:14:36.563
That's one subversive bolt-hole
that will give us no more trouble.


561
01:14:37.174 --> 01:14:40.405
He can't hide forever.
Sooner or later,


562
01:14:40.654 --> 01:14:42.451
Ali will be denounced.

563
01:14:42.894 --> 01:14:44.373
Congratulations.

564
01:14:45.014 --> 01:14:49.929
First it was children.
Now you attack empty shops.


565
01:14:50.694 --> 01:14:52.127
How courageous!

566
01:14:53.334 --> 01:14:58.966
It's not a shop, it's a meeting-place
for political activists and drunks.


567
01:14:59.214 --> 01:15:03.765
You'll be one of the first
to be hit by its closure.


568
01:15:04.054 --> 01:15:05.487
Follow me.

569
01:15:09.894 --> 01:15:13.967
That's it, follow the little captain.
And congratulations on the stripes.


570
01:15:19.774 --> 01:15:21.969
What are you doing here?

571
01:15:22.214 --> 01:15:25.047
This is men's business. Buzz off.

572
01:16:39.974 --> 01:16:41.168
Here, take these.

573
01:16:56.974 --> 01:17:00.603
When are the baths open for men?

574
01:17:02.454 --> 01:17:05.924
We're closing to clean them.

575
01:19:20.894 --> 01:19:26.127
Stop looking gloomy.
You'll miss your family when you leave.


576
01:19:27.574 --> 01:19:32.648
Look at me. I'm alone. No children,
no family, but I can't fly away.


577
01:19:33.014 --> 01:19:35.369
My wings have been clipped.

578
01:19:36.734 --> 01:19:39.202
Luckily I've this friend.

579
01:19:51.854 --> 01:19:55.529
<i>You help me laugh, cry,
forget and chatter</i>


580
01:19:57.734 --> 01:20:01.488
<i>I've given you my all
but what have you given me?</i>


581
01:20:01.734 --> 01:20:05.522
<i>You wicked bottle,
you dear old bottle</i>


582
01:20:07.014 --> 01:20:11.087
Salih, when does a boy become a man?

583
01:20:47.014 --> 01:20:50.290
<i>One mind for all- the President's</i>

584
01:20:51.734 --> 01:20:53.133
I don't agree.

585
01:21:25.534 --> 01:21:28.287
<i>Our minds - not the President's</i>

586
01:21:28.534 --> 01:21:29.853
Isn't that better?

587
01:21:31.054 --> 01:21:33.522
<i>I've given you my all</i>

588
01:21:36.414 --> 01:21:41.204
<i>But what have you given me,
dear old bottle?</i>


589
01:21:58.774 --> 01:22:01.686
I've had enough. I'm tired.

590
01:22:02.894 --> 01:22:05.727
And I'm getting old.

591
01:22:08.974 --> 01:22:10.965
No, Salih, you're still great.

592
01:23:10.094 --> 01:23:14.485
You can't deny it.
Someone saw you write it.


593
01:23:19.974 --> 01:23:23.649
Not only do walls have ears
but you see in the dark too.


594
01:23:23.934 --> 01:23:25.686
Don't act dumb.

595
01:23:26.534 --> 01:23:27.569
Take him away.

596
01:23:28.494 --> 01:23:29.688
Where are you taking him?

597
01:23:29.934 --> 01:23:32.494
Watch out or we'll close your shop.

598
01:23:32.734 --> 01:23:35.487
I'm to be a guest of the prison.

599
01:23:38.894 --> 01:23:42.045
Noura, tell your aunt
I've been called away.


600
01:23:42.414 --> 01:23:43.972
Ask her to wait.

601
01:25:39.334 --> 01:25:45.170
Try to be patient. Tomorrow
is another day. Nothing lasts for ever.


602
01:25:46.094 --> 01:25:48.449
One can't do the impossible.

603
01:25:53.894 --> 01:25:56.852
As you're stubborn and won't go
to the baths with you father,


604
01:25:57.094 --> 01:26:02.248
Leila must wash your hair.
I want you clean when I come back.


605
01:26:16.134 --> 01:26:18.329
That hurts.

606
01:26:18.774 --> 01:26:20.685
My mother is much gentler.

607
01:26:21.334 --> 01:26:22.733
Don't be a baby.

608
01:26:23.654 --> 01:26:25.053
I've finished.

609
01:26:27.574 --> 01:26:30.691
Why won't they let you into the baths?

610
01:26:31.654 --> 01:26:34.122
Have you a glint in your eye?

611
01:26:35.054 --> 01:26:37.249
I don't know. No one's told me.

612
01:26:47.614 --> 01:26:49.093
You're all wet.

613
01:26:49.854 --> 01:26:53.085
You should take off your clothes

614
01:26:53.334 --> 01:26:55.290
and do like in the baths.

615
01:27:21.574 --> 01:27:23.132
Is that how they do it?

616
01:27:23.814 --> 01:27:26.965
In the baths,
they take everything off.


617
01:27:27.454 --> 01:27:29.763
Ask Moncef and Mounir.

618
01:27:31.974 --> 01:27:33.043
I'm shy.

619
01:27:33.774 --> 01:27:36.288
You shouldn't be. 
It's not a sin.

620
01:27:36.614 --> 01:27:41.642
In the baths, women take off
their clothes and massage each other.


621
01:27:41.934 --> 01:27:44.767
I can show you, if you want.

622
01:28:08.894 --> 01:28:11.567
This is how it's done.

623
01:28:16.734 --> 01:28:18.326
No, don't do that.

624
01:28:18.654 --> 01:28:21.691
I'll slap you like my mother does me.

625
01:28:32.254 --> 01:28:36.452
Pack your things.
The sheikh will take you away.


626
01:30:16.174 --> 01:30:19.291
How long was Leila here?
Oh, thank you.


627
01:30:20.294 --> 01:30:25.493
May Allah make you
ever more prosperous and wealthy.


628
01:30:26.694 --> 01:30:29.731
And don't worry about a servant.

629
01:30:30.214 --> 01:30:34.002
I'll find you a harder-working maid.

630
01:30:34.254 --> 01:30:35.972
Please don't bother.

631
01:30:36.534 --> 01:30:39.412
Azzouz, you are so generous.

632
01:30:39.734 --> 01:30:43.090
You're so big-hearted and generous.

633
01:30:43.334 --> 01:30:45.564
Don't hesitate.

634
01:30:45.974 --> 01:30:49.046
Take me with you, sheikh.
Take me.


635
01:30:49.294 --> 01:30:50.966
Ask me to go with you.

636
01:30:54.294 --> 01:30:57.969
Go after him.
Find out where he lives.


637
01:30:58.214 --> 01:31:01.172
I couldn't.
He must make the first step.


638
01:31:17.534 --> 01:31:18.808
And money for the journey.

639
01:31:21.654 --> 01:31:22.928
Thank you.

640
01:31:26.014 --> 01:31:27.493
There's no doubt.

641
01:31:28.654 --> 01:31:30.724
That son of yours

642
01:31:31.774 --> 01:31:33.492
is grown up now.

643
01:31:45.254 --> 01:31:46.369
Come here.

644
01:31:46.854 --> 01:31:47.809
Hurry!

645
01:31:50.014 --> 01:31:51.083
Are you deaf?

646
01:31:51.454 --> 01:31:53.126
What's this? Defiance?

647
01:31:56.014 --> 01:31:56.969
Come here.

648
01:31:58.374 --> 01:32:01.969
Where are you going?
Come back down.


649
01:32:02.414 --> 01:32:05.565
Come down or I'll give you what for.

650
01:32:09.214 --> 01:32:10.727
And where are you going?

651
01:32:11.854 --> 01:32:15.369
Forgive me,
but I'm late for my injection.


652
01:32:22.294 --> 01:32:24.285
What's got into everybody?

653
01:32:24.734 --> 01:32:25.883
Come down!

654
01:32:28.254 --> 01:32:32.884
Come down or I'll kill you.
I mean it, I'll murder you.


655
01:32:45.334 --> 01:32:47.928
<i>Little bird, terrace bird</i>

656
01:32:48.174 --> 01:32:51.052
<i>Let him try his wings and fly</i>

657
01:32:51.294 --> 01:32:54.604
<i>He lives in paradise and he's free</i>

658
01:33:13.414 --> 01:33:16.451
<i>The little bird has grown and can fly</i>

659
01:33:19.934 --> 01:33:23.006
<i>The little bird dreams of flight</i>

660
01:33:23.254 --> 01:33:26.451
<i>Let him try his wings and fly</i>

661
01:33:45.534 --> 01:33:48.924
<i>He learnt to fly in Halfaouine</i>

662
01:33:51.934 --> 01:33:55.085
<i>One day he flew off
and left me sad</i>


663
01:33:55.334 --> 01:33:58.451
<i>Let him try his wings and fly</i>

664
01:34:17.214 --> 01:34:20.445
<i>I am the foolish
one and he the wise</i>

665
01:34:23.534 --> 01:34:26.606
<i>I still thought I was young</i>

666
01:34:26.854 --> 01:34:30.130
<i>Let him try his wings and fly</i>